<!channel>
Hey Everyone
This is the dashboard provided by the MoH to be used for visualizing the data collected by the surveillance response team .

You can view the live dashboard here (note, there is only sample/fake data for now):
<http://covid.fynsystems.com/cases>

You can access the code for the dashboard here:
<https://github.com/Ethiopia-COVID19/Covid19.ET>

All the data collected from the suspected cases forms will be imported and accessible to use and visualize in this project. I am working with the API team to get the API access integrated into the dashboard at the moment and will update the group once that is finished. In the meantime here is the model of the data we get back from the the Community surveillance form (1 of 4 forms) so you can see what the data we are working with looks like.

Form link:
<http://communityapp.sandboxaddis.com/>

Form data:
{
    “Woreda”: “Test Woreda”,
    “Longitude”: “YY”,
    “Region”: “Addis Ababa”,
    “Latitude”: “YY”,
    “sex”: “Female”,
    “Language”: “55",
    “SubcityOrZone”: “66",
    “Occupation”: “YY”,
    “FormStatus”: “Incomplete”,
    “cough”: true,
    “PhoneNo”: “4444”,
    “travleHx”: true,
    “checked”: false,
    “healthFacility”: true,
    “haveSex”: true,
    “occupation”: “Merchant(Animal)“,
    “HasSOB”: false,
    “fever”: true,
    “animalMarket”: true,
    “Kebele”: “TT”,
    “createdAt”: 1585335464387,
    “HouseNo”: “YY”,
    “Sefer”: “77",
    “updatedAt”: 1585335464387,
    “FirstName”: “ASDF”,
    “LastName”: “ASDF”,
    “Age”: “333”
}

You can begin working on the project by forking the repository, making your changes, then making a pull request against the main project.

*If you are looking to work with data and avoid using the API or code* I will see how we can get a sample export of the data. Let me know what formats work best for people.

*Let’s do a group check in here. Whenever you have a chance today, feel free to post in this channel with any ideas you have on improving the dashboard, suggesting alternative projects/dashboards, or share any in-progress or suggested non-dashboard visualizations.*

*One weak point we have at the moment is a lack of epidemiological experience in knowing which metrics and visualizations would be best to track for a use-case like this so any input there would be much appreciated as the current dashboard metrics we see in there are only what were supplied by the MoH.* We can then work on incorporating these metrics/visualizations into the current dashboard or alternative projects.

text: <@U01078QCG2C> Another suggestion. At the moment, Daily info is presented as a line chart. I would recommend a histogram plot instead as this is more consistent with the epidemic curve format epidemiologists typically use and little less crowded. See an example here: <http://sphweb.bumc.bu.edu/otlt/MPH-Modules/EP/EP713_DescriptiveEpi/EP713_DescriptiveEpi3.html>

text: It would also be very helpful to estimate a time-dependent effective reproduction number from the epidemic curve of cases identified. This could identify in real time the effect of control measures or other factors in the course of the epidemic. I'm linking to a paper describing a method for this used in the 2003 SARS epidemic. From a weibull distribution of the interval between generations, the probability that case i was infected by case j is calculated. This probability is then summed across all case i's to estimate an effective reproduction number for case j. The reproduction numbers for all case j's with the same date of onset are averaged to give an effective reproduction number as a function of date of onset. <https://academic.oup.com/aje/article/160/6/509/79472>

From a weibull distribution of the interval between generations, the probability that case i was infected by case j is calculated. This probability is then summed across all case i's to estimate an effective reproduction number for case j. The reproduction numbers for all case j's with the same date of onset are averaged to give an effective reproduction number as a function of date of onset.
